Last Button does not collect or store any personally identifiable information outside of Steam services.

Information we use:
SteamID (for multiplayer matchmaking and game sessions)
Steam username (display purposes in-game)
Steam avatar (display purposes in-game)
Gameplay session data (temporary, used only during matches)

What we do NOT do:
We do not sell or share user data
We do not collect personal information like real names, emails, or addresses
We do not use third-party analytics or tracking systems

Multiplayer:

The game uses Steam Networking services. This may involve:

IP address routing (handled by Steam)
Temporary session data required for online gameplay

We do not have access to or store this data ourselves.

Data storage:

No permanent player data is stored on our servers.

Third-party services:

The game uses Valve’s Steam platform. Please refer to:
https://store.steampowered.com/privacy_agreement/
